# Snyk (https://snyk.io) policy file
version: v1.5.0

# Exclude the arcade screenshot harness from Snyk Code (SAST).
#
# scripts/screenshot-games.js is a developer-only tool: it serves ./dist over a
# tiny loopback-only HTTP server (127.0.0.1:4173) so a local Playwright/Chromium
# can capture deterministic before/after PNGs of the games. It is never shipped,
# never imported by the site, and not wired into npm scripts or CI.
#
# Snyk Code flags four issues here, all acceptable for this context:
#   - HIGH/LOW Path Traversal: the request handler already contains resolved
#     paths to ./dist (rejects anything that escapes with 403), and the write
#     path is the operator's own chosen output dir plus a hardcoded filename.
#   - MEDIUM Cleartext HTTP / no rate-limiting: inherent to a single-user
#     loopback dev server; HTTPS and rate-limiting middleware would be
#     over-engineering for a throwaway local screenshot script.
#
# Per-finding Snyk Code ignores require the Snyk platform (unavailable in this
# local-only setup), so the dev script is excluded from Code analysis wholesale.
exclude:
  code:
    - scripts/screenshot-games.js
